HEADWORD: Monticle
<hw>Mon"ti*cle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>monticulus</ets>, dim. of <ets>mons</ets>, <ets>montis</ets>,
mountain: cf. F. <ets>monticule</ets>. See <er>Mount</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>A little mount; a hillock; a small elevation
or prominence.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>monticule</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monticulate</ent>⟦br⟧
